  "texts": [
    "I. INTRODUCTIONG RAPH data is extensively utilized across a diverse range of domains, owing to its capability to represent complex structural relationships among various entities in the real world [1], [2], [3].",
    "Notable applications include, but are not limited to, social networks [4], [5], chemical molecular structures [6], transportation systems [7], and recommender systems [8], [9].",
    "However, the exponential growth of data volume in these applications makes the management and processing of largescale graph data a complex and challenging task.",
    "A particularly demanding aspect is the computational requirements associated with training graph neural networks (GNNs) on large-scale graph datasets [10].",
    "These challenges are more pronounced in scenarios that require training multiple GNNs, such as hyper-parameter optimization [11], continual learning [12] and neural architecture search [13], etc."
  ],
